node.text: The new album is named for West’s late mother, who passed away in 2007. While DONDA explores a wider range of genres than his previous album Jesus is King, it features some of the religious themes that West has pivoted to in his recent music. A partial tracklist posted by West ahead of the release listed titles like “Pure Souls” and “Keep My Spirit Alive.” The album will be available for purchase and streaming on July 23rd.

node.text: Founded by Jeff Bezos, space travel company Blue Origin completed its first passenger flight on July 20. The rocket, named New Shepard, carried Bezos and three other passengers more than 65-miles above Earth, just to the boundary of space, known as the Kármán line. Watch our latest episode of HBNN to learn more.

node.title: @jeffbezos Completes His First Flight into Space

node.text: Continuing to make sure that fans have something to celebrate whether they’re courtside or elsewhere, @oculus is partnering with HYPEBEAST News Network to share the top NBA-related news, keeping you up to date on all things basketball all season long. In this episode, we take a look at the new promo for ‘Space Jam: A New Legacy,’ starring LeBron James, in addition to the movie’s merchandise drops from Nike and Converse.

node.text: The Porsche 911 has become “the” benchmark for all sports cars but is also impossible for rival automakers to replicate it, maintaining its value over time reselling for double and even triple its retail cost over time. Find out why in our latest installment of 'Behind the HYPE.'

node.text:
@hypebeaststyle: @mancity and @puma have unveiled their new away kit, paying tribute to the club's Cityzens Giving initiative which aims to use football to educate and provide safe water access to communities in need. The club’s crest, PUMA cat, and sponsor logos feature iridescent colors, resembling the effect of light breaking through water droplets. PUMA has also reduced the amount of water waste and consumption during the manufacturing of the kit. The new Manchester City Away Kit is now available from both the PUMA and Manchester City websites.⁠⁠
Photo: PUMA

node.text:
@hypeart: Chicago-born, Oregon-based fine artist and designer Julian Gaines, better known as @juworkingonprojects, has debuted his 'Painting the Blueprint' solo show at Lower Manhattan’s Steven Harvey Fine Art Projects. Consisting of five large-scale canvas paintings, the show spotlights Ganes’ “New Black History” ethos, spotlighting underappreciated-yet-influential individuals in Black American history while also paying homage to iconic Black thinkers. The exhibit will be open until September 3.⁠⁠
Photo: Nick Llanton/HYPEBEAST

node.text:
@hypebeastkicks: @virgilabloh broke sneaker headlines with the reveal of “The 50” Dunk Low collection. Of the 50 pairs dropping this August, the 04 and 06 colorways have revealed themselves by way of detailed imagery. A majority of the capsule's pairs feature similar upper constructions. The leather bases are coordinated with white finishes on the quarters, toe boxes, and collars while the Swooshes and overlays are dyed in a light gray hue. Differentiating pops of color are used throughout the tounges, hang tags, midsole molds, and secondary lace sets.⁠⁠
Photo: @leaked.sneaks

node.text:
@hypeart: The Royal Academy of Art has partnered with a new cultural organization, called @theartofldn, to breathe life back into London’s city center. 'The Piccadilly Art Takeover' is the largest public art initiative the city has ever seen and is supported by a number of groups. Walk the streets to find 13 vibrantly painted crossings — the most art crossings ever in one place in the UK — accompanied by 30 equally eye-catching flags, and a special AR experience via mobile phones. 'The Piccadilly Art Takeover' runs from July 21 to August 31. Hit the link in bio for more info.⁠⁠
Photo: Heart Of London Business Alliance

@hypebeastkicks: @nike is continuing its slew of @nba Dunk Low releases in celebration of the 75th anniversary of the upcoming season. The iteration features a Bulls-Esque colorway equipped with “Sail” toeboxes and quarter panels combined with “Chile Red” mudguards and black Swooshes creating almost like a reverse "Black Toe." The shoes are expected to arrive sometime in October in time for the start of the new NBA season.⁠⁠

@hypebeaststyle: @patta_nl celebrates the legendary @jimihendrix and his illustrious career with a special range of apparel. Included is a selection of tees, hoodies, and a short-sleeved button-down, with select pieces nodding to iconic performances, as well as his groups, The Jimi Hendrix Experience and the Band of Gypsies. The Patta x Authentic Hendrix LLC collection is set to drop on July 30 via the Patta webstore.⁠⁠
Photo: @piet_oosterbeek

@hypebeastkicks: @jumpman23 is set to bring back the clean Air Jordan 11 "Cool Grey" this holiday season. Debuted in 2000 and last retroed in 2010, the “Cool Grey” has long enjoyed status as one of the most popular non-OG Air Jordan 11 colorways, and this second retro aims to provide an accurate re-creation of the 2000 original. Expect these to release on December 11 for $225 USD.⁠⁠
Photo: @fxxkvlogvi

node.text:
@hypebeastcarclub: @audi has unveiled its 2022 Dakar Rally RSQ E-Tron Off-Roader. The monstrous EV racer comes equipped with a turbocharged 2.0-liter inline-four and runs on a 50-kWh battery capable of 671 HP. Aesthetically, the electrified off-road beast is constructed of a carbon fiber casing that features a faux single-frame grille paired with bright red accents that highlight the monster wheels and rims, giving the car a more intimidating look. Hit the link in bio for more info.⁠⁠
Photo: Audi

node.text:
@hypefoods: @krispykreme has teamed up with @microsoft for an @xbox-themed donut. Named the Nexus Level, the new delicacy features Xbox’s iconic logo. More excitingly, those who purchase a box of a dozen Nexus Level donuts will receive a month of the Xbox Game Pass Ultimate membership as well as a chance to win an Xbox Series S. Get your hands on them from August 2 to 22. ⁠
Photo: Krispy Kreme

node.text:
@hypebeastkicks: @nike’s Air Force 1 Low has surfaced with a bold new twist: UV-reactive detailing. Key to the design is a Swoosh that shifts from white to chilly ice blue like the translucent outsole, and a heel that transforms from white to vibrant pink. Expect it to drop at retailers like @solebox on September 17 for $120 USD.⁠
Photo: Solebox

node.text:
@hypeart: @glucklawfirm, the law firm representing @futuradosmil, has given an update about the ongoing case involving @thenorthface. The outerwear label filed a legal motion claiming that Futura has no trademark rights on the logo, with the motion centered around the basis that the artist “uses varied artistic versions of it.” Find out more details via the link in bio.⁠
Photo: HYPEBEAST
